[Student "S"]
{EAST has an opening hand, 15 points and five \Ss. But NORTH beat him to the punch, 
so he overcalls 1\S. 

WEST has 11 points, and if EAST had opened she would make a Limit Raise to 3\S. 

But when replying to an Overcall, the strength needs to be a little higher. In Deal 1 it was OK to 
pass a 1\S Overcall with 6 points, here it is correct to just raise to 2\S with 11 points.

EAST actually has a strong Overcall so he bids 4\S.}

